.TH COREDNS 8 "2025-02-17" "coredns" "CoreDNS with ruledforward plugin"
.SH NAME
coredns \- CoreDNS DNS server with ruledforward plugin
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B coredns
[\fI\-conf\fR \fIFILE\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBcoredns\fR is a single binary that runs CoreDNS with the
\fBruledforward\fR plugin compiled in. It is the same as CoreDNS but includes
rule-based forwarding: match query names against groups (geosite, AdGuard,
inline rules) and either forward to upstreams or return empty (NODATA).
.PP
All standard CoreDNS command-line options apply. The main one is:
.TP
.BR \-conf " \fIFILE\fR"
Path to the Corefile (default: \fICorefile\fR in current directory).
.PP
In the Corefile, use the \fBruledforward\fR plugin block. See the
documentation and examples in the project repository.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/coredns/Corefile
Typical location for the Corefile when run as a system service.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/coredns
Default binary location when installed from packages.
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation: https://github.com/hr3lxphr6j/coredns-ruledforward
.PP
CoreDNS manual: https://coredns.io/manual/
